  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1996-06-27", 
    "text": "Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow the deduction as capital expenditures of the following costs incurred for replanting edible crops for human consumption which were lost by reason of freezing temperatures, disease, drought, pests, or casualty: (1) replanting costs; (2) 80 percent of the special replanting costs of such replanting; (3) the removal of lost plants; and (4) and preproductive costs."
  }, 
